document.title: Maryland Physical Education Framework: Pre-Kindergarten Through High School

AB0E57601E584A72A66C9362BC702645.description:
Explains the
relationship between
self-expression and
lifelong enjoyment
through physical
activity.

1AAD503E55B649F69355EE7B9B9E09DF.description:
Identifies why self-selected physical
activities create
enjoyment.

9377D11182654840932847C2E527EE5A.description:
Shows that skills will
develop over time with
appropriate practice.

50C320EC23ED4A3ABD26A78512DB0A31.description:
Generates positive
strategies such as
offering suggestions or
assistance, leading or
following others, and
providing possible
solutions when faced
with a group challenge.

A7F6704F9073482DB23A88A8867FF368.description:
Identifies positive
mental and emotional
aspects of participating
in a variety of physical
activities.

0B67E6B59A2A42A6840393FADD6C82AA.description:
Identifies different
types of physical
activities and describes
how each exerts a
positive effect on
health.

B5DFC8F0ECCF4E018DC627494EE8CDF0.description: Recognizes the Value of Physical Activity

19BC5798D4AE432B81B5A58427A993B9.description:
Identifies the rules and
etiquette for activities.

1976A528AAD1474897DE8BECD223F23F.description:
Cooperates with a small
group of classmates.

537B178E5B3343A793A66AB6F2F7A076.description:
Accepts differences
among classmates in
physical development,
maturation, and skill
level by providing
encouragement and
positive feedback.

CD8059D5C0EC4B93BB00DF6E94406F13.description:
Demonstrates self-responsibility by
implementing specific
corrective feedback to
improve performance.

DFA7BCBAAAF3420E92551442578F7385.description:
Identifies and uses
appropriate strategies
to self-reinforce
positive fitness
behaviors.

A49D023848F644D78CD4F032DEE9C0EA.description:
Exhibits personal
responsibility by using
appropriate etiquette,
demonstrating respect
for facilities, and
exhibiting safe
behaviors.

BBB210563C8B49BC8D24623EAAEAF4D3.description:
Describes and
demonstrates the
difference between
dynamic and static
stretches.

F774CA7FE4A64505AC1A16F836386026.description:
Adjusts physical activity
based on quantity of
exercise needed for a
minimal health standard
and/or optimal
functioning based on
current fitness level.

869E571CA1BC43129DE668750D994F41.description:
Distinguishes between
health-related and skill-related fitness
components.

A9893DF4AC4941AE9C12A48849F30B41.description:
Participates in a variety
of moderate to vigorous
strength and endurance
fitness activities
(Pilates, resistance
training, body weight
training, free weight
training, dual and
individual sports,
martial arts, or aquatic
activities).

643662D5B0F744259456E025811C6C01.description:
Identifies barriers
related to maintaining a
physically active
lifestyle and seeks
solutions for eliminating
those barriers.

A2A26F84A3194E3FA9863FE183639CA2.description: Health-Enhancing Level of Physical Activity and Fitness

D6EF24CBC79E4E0380406E6CA6147312.description:
Analyzes an activity and
makes adjustments to
ensure the safety of self
and others.

BD74073A0133432AA34553C54A8B79C2.description:
Identifies and applies
Newton's Laws of
Motion to various
dance or movement
activities.

6AE24F72731C4790BC359D0945B07EFC.description:
Selects the correct
defensive play based on
the situation.

B71335E578D14A0B9EA1BDC73A63EB6E.description:
Uses a variety of shots
to hit to open space.

6CB531A0D0E54B3DBF54346253CA34BB.description:
Varies the speed and/or
trajectory of the shot
based on location of the
object in relation to the
target.

CA722C790A1C46DDB8A674EFB2139658.description:
Selects offensive shot
based on opponent’s
location.

BCB07608CAF146F5B644E6833FD6973B.description:
Creates open space in
net or wall games with a
long-handled
implement by varying
force and direction and
by moving opponent
from side to side.

98DD903FD1354DADA1F252D41DBFF1D0.description:
Transitions from
offense to defense or
defense to offense by
recovering quickly and
communicating with
teammates.

F5E965E9050444B5B7287056CAEA5F90.description:
Reduces open space by
not allowing the catch
(denial) or anticipating
the speed of the object
and person for the
purpose of interception
or deflection.

988DDDE3BA544AACB1C48E22B3AAF19A.description:
Reduces open space on
defense by staying
close to the opponent
as they near the goal.

0DB0FE5C0B184C77B771CBCED69DF1E4.description:
Reducing Space -
Changing Size and
Shape

2345B1BD4A4A4021A2AF53F6355232FE.description:
Executes at least two of
the following offensive
tactics to create open
space: uses a variety of
passes, pivots and
fakes; give and go.

C1DB450D161A4758903637182229DEAC.description:
Reduces open space in
combination with
movement concepts.

7BA9921871334F2FBC5BBD034F8126E1.description:
Demonstrates correct
technique for a variety
of skills in one self-selected individual
performance activity.

3E958787F09B4CCDB341A70413465539.description:
Demonstrates correct
technique for a variety
of skills in one self-selected outdoor
activity.

02EA06BB693C4E0CBB825AE02BCC330D.description:
Catches, with a mature
pattern, from different
trajectories, using a
variety of objects in
small-sided game play
while using an
implement.

B89484BACC2E427A9988EBB87352F389.description:
Catching with a Short
or Long-Handled
Implement

64C4417C32B0494A875857AB04398F9F.description:
Strikes a pitched ball
with an implement to
open space in a variety
of practice tasks.

15D9650346094D16B09DBB5F98EF674C.description:
Consistently propels an
object for target games.

C908C0488BE240FB9CEE54901EC96981.description:
Two-hand volleys with
control in a dynamic
environment.

36FAA4E756F84718B25ABFCB0E64579E.description:
Forehand and backhand
volleys with a mature
pattern and control
using a short handled
implement.

7EE267BA7408423D9381A25AFA6CB6C5.description:
Transfers weight with
correct timing using
low-to-high striking
pattern with a short-handled implement on
the forehand side.

AEFF592A6FB844C0987D4ECFA8E1526B.description:
Demonstrates the
mature form of
forehand and backhand
strokes with a long-handled implement in
net games.

016EAD3F1E8F4BF8A9FAA563F86D8770.description:
Strikes with a mature
overhand pattern in a
dynamic environment
for net or wall games.

B8A97FA8B07243A78E52E4F58912D287.description:
Consistently executes
an underhand serve
with a mature pattern
to a predetermined
target for net and wall
games.

9821FA9831A749F3AA7E449149DD9DC1.description:
Slides in all directions
while on defense
without crossing feet.

C912E59177814F7D9D0B7EB8FB14F8D1.description:
Shoots on goal with
power and accuracy in
small-sided game play.

43D751E3B2774CE18E3FFD19851C3D6C.description:
Foot-dribbles or
dribbles with an
implement combined
with passing in a variety
of practice tasks.

260882DF6C0C40C8AA245E04AB9E284E.description:
Dribbles with dominant
and non-dominant
hands using a change of
speed and direction in a
variety of practice
tasks.

C9028D2CA194456FA05A5BAAE2EE2411.description:
Performs the following
offensive skills with
defensive pressure:
pivot, give and go, and
fakes.

4290E3E7222F407488F4B6EE27134BBA.description:
Executes at least one of
the following designed
to create open space
during small-sided game
play: pivots, fakes, jab
steps.

E49B3FD1B1604C5FABD0284DFB602DEA.description:
Throws, while moving, a
leading pass to a
moving receiver.

922B9896CC4D45A2B43BD723AC4D6A78.description:
Passes and receives
with feet while
changing direction and
speed with
competency.

978C6C0CD9E24B19A8FE6F91A65EE3C8.description:
Catches a variety of
objects from different
trajectories with a
mature pattern in small-sided game play.

2F52B3A5EC0145EE845FF5A712790C5D.description:
Throws with a mature
pattern for distance or
power appropriate to
the activity in a dynamic
environment.

230E3D4351394BA8A47B37C863F6639F.description:
Demonstrates correct
rhythm and pattern for
one dance form.
